ant="bold" mathsize="normal"><mml:mi>G</mml:mi></mml:mstyle></mml:math></inline-formula> Genomic relationship matrix is computed assuming than only presence or absence of the alternative allele could be known for the remaining, <italic>i.e.</italic>, although the organism was polyploid, Genomic relationship matrix is computed assuming than only presence or absence of the alternative allele can be ascertained. (a) additive architecture; (b) dominant architecture.</p>
