        <list-item>
          <p><inline-formula><mml:math id="me78"><mml:mrow><mml:mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal"><mml:mi>G</mml:mi><mml:mi>T</mml:mi></mml:mstyle></mml:mrow></mml:math></inline-formula>: The true genotype, <italic>i.e.</italic>, number of copies of the alternative allele, was known without error and all SNPs were used. In this approach Equation <inline-formula><mml:math id="me79"><mml:mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal"><mml:mi>M</mml:mi></mml:mstyle></mml:math></inline-formula> (<xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="eq1">Equation 1</xref>) has elements varying between 0 and 8.</p>
